{{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 22''' is the 22nd day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . == Events == * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|1189|ja|1189|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|November 2|ja|11月2日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} appointed {{ill|Kōzaisei Kiyoshige|ja|葛西清重|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} as the chief administrator (奥州総奉行), thereby consolidating control over Ōshu. * {{ill|Tenwa (Japan)|ja|天和|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|1683|ja|1683|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – In Kyoto, the wife of the great Buddhist priest (大経師) – known as {{ill|O-san and Tedai Shigehei|ja|おさんと手代茂兵衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} – was executed for adultery. This incident provided material for works such as {{ill|Nishikaze’s|ja|西鶴|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} "Kōshoku Gonin Onna" and {{ill|Chikamatsu’s|ja|近松|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} "Daikyōshi Mukireki". * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – The lord of the Aizu domain, {{ill|Matsudaira Katamori|ja|松平容保|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , opened his castle ({{Tsurugajo|qq=}} ) by "opening the castle" ceremony; Aizu later surrendered to the imperial forces.
