|November 10]] ） – In Kyoto, the wife of the great Buddhist priest (大経師) – known as {{ill|O-san and Tedai Shigehei|ja|おさんと手代茂兵衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/O-san and Tedai Shigehei|qq=}} – was executed for adultery. This incident provided material for works such as {{ill|Nishikaze’s|ja|西鶴|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishikaze’s|qq=}} "Kōshoku Gonin Onna" and {{ill|Chikamatsu’s|ja|近松|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikamatsu’s|qq=}} "Daikyōshi Mukireki". * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}} [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ） – The lord of the Aizu domain, [[:en:Matsudaira Katamori|Matsudaira Katamori]] , opened his castle ({{Tsurugajo|qq=}} ) by "opening the castle" ceremony; Aizu later surrendered to the imperial forces.
== Births == * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1852|ja|1852|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1852|qq=}} [[:en:November 3|November 3]] ） – The future Emperor [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Meiji]] , the 122nd emperor († {{ill|1912|ja|1912|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1912|qq=}} ).
