lendar]] [[:en:1683|1683]] [[:en:November 10|November 10]] ） – In Kyoto, the wife of the great Buddhist priest (大経師) – known as {{ill|O-san and Tedai Shigehei|ja|おさんと手代茂兵衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/O-san and Tedai Shigehei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} – was executed for adultery. This incident provided material for works such as {{ill|Nishikaze’s|ja|西鶴|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishikaze’s|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 井原西鶴}} "Kōshoku Gonin Onna" and {{ill|Chikamatsu’s|ja|近松|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikamatsu’s|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近松門左衛門}} "Daikyōshi Mukireki". * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}} [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ） – The lord of the Aizu domain, [[:en:Matsudaira Katamori|Matsudaira Katamori]] , opened his castle ({{Tsurugajo|qq=}} ) by "opening the castle" ceremony; Aizu later surrendered to the imperial forces.
== Births == * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1852|ja|1852|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1852|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:November 3|November 3]] ） – The future Emperor [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Meiji]] , the 122nd emperor († {{ill|1912|ja|1912|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1912|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ōchō|Ōchō]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1311|1311]] [[:en:November 3|November 3]] ） – [[:en:Hōjō Morotoki|Hojo Ujitoki]] , the 10th shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (* [[:en:1275|1275]] ). * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 安永 (元号)}} 2nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1773|1773]] [[:en:October 22|October 22]] ） – {{ill|Tanuma Yoshinori|ja|田沼意明|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanuma Yoshinori|qq=}} , the first lord of the Mutsu Shimomura domain (* {{ill|1796|ja|1796|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1796|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ).
